## 7. Summary Table: Inflation Effects on Housing Market Stakeholders

| Stakeholder           | Inflation Effect                                                                 | Implications                                                      |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Homeowners**        | Home values rise; fixed-rate mortgage payments become cheaper in real terms     | Increased wealth; protection against inflation                   |
| **First-time Buyers** | Higher home prices and mortgage rates; reduced purchasing power                 | Affordability challenges; larger down payments required          |
| **Renters**           | Rising rents due to increased landlord costs and demand                         | Increased housing cost burden; affordability stress              |
| **Investors**         | Property values and rents increase; leverage amplifies returns                  | Attractive inflation hedge; potential for higher cash flow       |
| **Lenders**           | Higher interest rates; increased loan amounts due to higher prices             | Potential for increased profits; risk from adjustable-rate loans |
| **Builders/Developers**| Increased material and labor costs; supply constraints                          | Higher construction costs; reduced new housing supply            |
| **Policy Makers**     | Need to balance inflation control with housing market stability                 | Challenges in setting interest rates and housing policies        |

